<body>
<h1 class="title">Mascot for NUS IT Security Awareness Campaign</h1>
<div class="cs3-container">
  <p>Create and design a Mascot character, for branding, which can be used in IT Security Awareness Campaign. </p>
  <h2 class="cs3-heading">Context</h2>
  <p>
    This mascot character could be used as character on a website, an email, a poster, an intranet article, videos, and e-Learnings and so on to promote adopting good security habits. This mascot would potentially be converted to 3D format for live size representation. 
    <br/>
    <br/>
    It should be possible to resize it depending on the action, so a high quality graphics format is required. It should both work on a computer screen and on a printed poster.   
    <br/>
    <br/>
    The target audience of mascot are students and staff of NUS. 
    <br/>
  </p>
  <h2 class="cs3-heading">Prizes</h2>
  <p>First prize:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Apple iPad (32GB) and</li>
    <li>Apple Pencil (1st Generation) and</li>
    <li>12-months Adobe Creative Cloud for Individual Complete All Apps membership</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Second prize:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Capitaland Voucher and</li>
    <li>12-months Adobe Creative Cloud for Individual Complete All Apps membership</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Third prize:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Capitaland Voucher and</li>
    <li>12-months Adobe Creative Cloud for Individual Complete All Apps membership</li>
  </ul>

<% if current_user == nil || !@challenge_statement.id.in?(current_user.joined_challenge_statement) %>
  <% if @challenge_statement.is_open %>
    <%=  button_to "Join Challenge Statement", join_challenge_statement_path(@challenge_statement), class: "button" %>
  <% else %>
    <%= "Thank you for your interest in Creation 2020, currently we are no longer accepting submissions for this Challenge Statement!" %>
  <% end %>
<%  end %>

<div style="text-align: center;">
<% if current_user != nil && @challenge_statement.id.in?(current_user.joined_challenge_statement) %>
  <% if @challenge_statement.is_open %>
    <%= link_to "Download brief and template", rails_blob_path(@challenge_statement.zip, disposition: 'attachment'), :class => "button" %>
    <br/>
    <br/>
    <%= link_to "Submit a submission", all_submissions_path, :class => "button" %>
  <% else %>
    <%= "Thank you for your interest in Creation 2020, currently we are no longer accepting submissions for this Challenge Statement!" %>
  <% end %>
<% end %>

<% if user_signed_in? %>
  <% if current_user.admin %>
    <%= button_to 'Edit', edit_challenge_statement_path(@challenge_statement), :method => :get %>
    <% if @challenge_statement.is_open %>
      <%= button_to 'Close Challenge Statement', close_challenge_statement_path(@challenge_statement), data: { confirm: 'Are you sure?' }%>
    <% else %>
      <%= button_to 'Open Challenge Statement', close_challenge_statement_path(@challenge_statement),  data: { confirm: 'Are you sure?' }%>
    <% end %>
  <% end %>
<% end %>
<br/>
<br/>
<%= link_to 'Back', challenge_statements_path %>
</div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
